how can i prevent a yeast infection my doctor just put me on some strong antibiotics for a sinus infection and every time i get put on antibiotics i get a yeast infection is there anyway to prevent it from happening your doctor should have advised you to take acidopholus with your antibiotics every single time acidopholus helps keep up your levels of good bacteria to prevent this problem it is so common after about a year of the same problem i finally heard this advice and it's amazing i take about a day every day i'm on the antibiotics and a few extras in the following days acidopholus is found with other vitamins supplements at most drugstores store it in the refrigerator to keep it as fresh and potent as possible best of luck to you Psoriasis Folic acid Chronic fatigue syndrome Common cold Garlic Acne Nutrition Antibiotic Pneumonia Candidiasis Antibiotic resistance Clostridium difficile Cephalexin Group A streptococcal infection Bacteria Cystic fibrosis Guinea pig Breastfeeding Prostate cancer Milk Traumatic brain injury Urinary incontinence Gonorrhoea Lactobacillus acidophilus Cystoscopy Hepatitis Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Fancy rat Streptococcus pneumoniae Cellulitis Vitamin C Cyanocobalamin Cirrhosis Upper respiratory tract infection Isotretinoin Endocarditis Legionellosis Medical analysis of circumcision Ciprofloxacin Mouth ulcer Vancomycin Gastroesophageal reflux disease Chlamydophila pneumoniae Livestock Veganism Rocky Mountain spotted fever Domestic rabbit Anthrax Bubonic plague Riboflavin Crohn's disease Bacterial meningitis Conjunctivitis Coeliac disease Wound Traditional Chinese medicine Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Lyme disease Eczema Protein-energy malnutrition Retinol Ethanol Transformation (genetics) Foodborne illness Pasteurization Coronary heart disease Antiviral drug Stomach cancer Herpes simplex virus Helicobacter pylori Brewing Dairy farming Infectious disease Warfarin Aspergillosis Otitis externa Hamster Hormone replacement therapy (trans) S